---
layout: landing.njk
title: OPE
---

<!-- Hero -->
<section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-zinc-900 py-20 sm:py-28">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none opacity-30" style="background: radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 50% at 50% -10%, #36b49f, transparent), radial-gradient(ellipse 40% 40% at 80% 100%, #DBFF75, transparent)"></div>
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 relative">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <span class="rounded-full bg-emerald-400/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-emerald-400 ring-1 ring-inset ring-emerald-400/20">Draft Specification v0.1</span>
      <h1 class="mt-6 text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Portable subscriptions for the open web</h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-zinc-400 leading-relaxed max-w-lg">OPE is a portable entitlement layer that lets readers access gated content across any app, any feed format, any browser, and any platform. Subscribe once, read anywhere — in your feed reader, on the web, or through a broker bundle.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="{{ '/ope/spec/' | url }}" class="rounded-full bg-emerald-500 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-emerald-400 no-underline transition-colors">Read the Spec</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/shellen/open-portable-entitlement" class="rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-400 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-400/20 hover:text-white hover:ring-zinc-400/40 no-underline transition-colors">View on GitHub</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Principles -->
<section class="border-b border-zinc-900/5 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-10">
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M10 18.3s6.7-3.3 6.7-8.3V4.2L10 1.7 3.3 4.2V10c0 5 6.7 8.3 6.7 8.3z"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Entitlement, not payments</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">OPE proves you're allowed in. Payment processors handle money. Clean separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="2" y="6" width="16" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M13 18V4a2 2 0 0 0-2-2H9a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Truly portable</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Your subscription works in any OPE-compatible reader. No platform lock-in.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M3.3 9.2a7.5 7.5 0 0 1 7.5 7.5"/><path d="M3.3 3.3a13.3 13.3 0 0 1 13.3 13.3"/><circle cx="4.2" cy="15.8" r=".8"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Works with any feed</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">RSS, Atom, JSON Feed, AT Protocol. OPE extends what you already use.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-lg bg-emerald-400/10 text-emerald-500 mb-4">
          <svg width="20" height="20" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14.2 17.5v-1.7a3.3 3.3 0 0 0-3.3-3.3H4.2a3.3 3.3 0 0 0-3.3 3.3v1.7"/><circle cx="7.5" cy="5.8" r="3.3"/><path d="M19.2 17.5v-1.7a3.3 3.3 0 0 0-2.5-3.2"/><path d="M13.3 2.6a3.3 3.3 0 0 1 0 6.5"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Publisher-controlled</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Publishers issue grants and control access. Their content, their rules.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Design Philosophy -->
<section class="py-20" id="how-it-works">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Design Philosophy</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Four layers, cleanly separated</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">OPE occupies the space between content distribution and payment processing. Each concern stays independent.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-400 mb-2">Layer 1</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Content</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Articles, media, and resources. Created and hosted by the publisher.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-400 mb-2">Layer 2</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Distribution</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Feed formats (RSS, Atom, JSON Feed, ATProto) that catalog and deliver previews.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-emerald-400/30 bg-emerald-400/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-emerald-500 mb-2">Layer 3 — OPE</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Entitlement</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">Verification that a reader has the right to access content. Portable across apps.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5">
        <div class="text-xs font-medium text-zinc-400 mb-2">Layer 4</div>
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">Payments</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">How money changes hands. Stripe, x402, Lightning, or anything else. Out of scope.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Flow -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">The Flow</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">From feed to full content</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">Five steps from discovering an article in your reader to reading the full thing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-5 gap-8">
      {% for step in [{n:"1",t:"Feed",d:"Reader fetches a feed and finds OPE-gated items with preview content."},{n:"2",t:"Discovery",d:"Reader fetches /.well-known/ope to learn the publisher's capabilities."},{n:"3",t:"Authenticate",d:"Reader initiates OAuth 2.0 with PKCE. User logs in with the publisher."},{n:"4",t:"Grant",d:"Publisher issues a signed grant token proving entitlement."},{n:"5",t:"Read",d:"Reader presents the token and retrieves full content. Done."}] %}
      <div>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 rounded-full ring-1 ring-zinc-900/10 text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-500 mb-4">{{ step.n }}</div>
        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-1">{{ step.t }}</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500 leading-relaxed">{{ step.d }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Code Example -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 mb-4">Simple discovery, powerful access</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mb-6 leading-relaxed">Publishers expose a single well-known endpoint. Reader apps handle the rest — OAuth, token management, content retrieval — all standardized.</p>
        <dl class="space-y-3">
          {% for item in [{k:"Discovery",v:"JSON manifest at a well-known URL"},{k:"Auth",v:"OAuth 2.0 with PKCE, consent, dynamic registration"},{k:"Tokens",v:"JWT, PASETO, or Macaroons — API or cookie transport"},{k:"Content",v:"Single item or batch retrieval, HTTP 402 signaling"},{k:"Web",v:"Cookie-based grants, browser unlock, cross-publisher SSO"},{k:"Feeds",v:"Non-breaking extensions with unlock URLs"}] %}
          <div class="flex gap-3 text-sm">
            <dt class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 whitespace-nowrap">{{ item.k }}</dt>
            <dd class="text-zinc-600">{{ item.v }}</dd>
          </div>
          {% endfor %}
        </dl>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-8 lg:mt-0 bg-zinc-900 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)] text-xs">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-3 border-b border-white/5">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/10"></span>
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/10"></span>
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-white/10"></span>
          <span class="ml-2 text-zinc-500 text-xs font-[family-name:var(--font-mono)]">/.well-known/ope</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="p-5 overflow-x-auto m-0 text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">{
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"version"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"0.1"</span>,
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"oauth_server"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server"</span>,
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"entitlement"</span>: {
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"grant_url"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/api/entitlement/grant"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"token_format"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"jwt"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"token_mode"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"portable"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"default_ttl_seconds"</span>: <span class="text-sky-300">3600</span>
  },
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"content"</span>: {
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"endpoint_template"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/api/content/{id}"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"batch_endpoint"</span>: <span class="text-amber-300">"https://example.com/api/content/batch"</span>,
    <span class="text-emerald-400">"formats_available"</span>: [<span class="text-amber-300">"html"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"markdown"</span>]
  },
  <span class="text-emerald-400">"grants_supported"</span>: [<span class="text-amber-300">"subscription"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"gift"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"per_item"</span>, <span class="text-amber-300">"broker"</span>]
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Audience -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5" id="for-whom">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Who It's For</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Built for the entire ecosystem</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {% for card in [{t:"Publishers",d:"Keep full control of your content and subscriptions while making them work everywhere.",items:["Add OPE metadata to your existing feeds","Expose a single discovery endpoint","Use the reference gateway or build your own","Support any payment processor you want","WordPress, Ghost, Substack migration paths"]},{t:"Reader Apps &amp; Browsers",d:"Give your users seamless access to gated content from any OPE-enabled publisher — in-app or on the web.",items:["Detect OPE extensions in any feed format","Manage per-publisher OAuth sessions","Show rich previews with content metadata","Batch retrieval for fast offline sync","Browser unlock via cookies and HTTP 402","Unified subscription view across publishers"]},{t:"Brokers",d:"Create subscription bundles across multiple publishers. Like cable bundles, but for the open web.",items:["Aggregate entitlements across publishers","Issue broker grant tokens with Macaroons","Capability attenuation for scoped access","Single sign-on for multi-publisher access","Enable new business models"]}] %}
      <div class="rounded-2xl border border-zinc-900/5 p-6">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-2">{{ card.t }}</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mb-4">{{ card.d }}</p>
        <ul class="space-y-1.5 list-none p-0">
          {% for item in card.items %}
          <li class="text-sm text-zinc-500 flex gap-2"><span class="text-emerald-500 mt-1.5 shrink-0">·</span> {{ item }}</li>
          {% endfor %}
        </ul>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Grant Types -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Flexible Access</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Eight grant types, one protocol</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">OPE doesn't prescribe how entitlements are earned — it standardizes how they're proven.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-3">
      {% for g in [{t:"Subscription",d:"Recurring access to all content"},{t:"Per-item",d:"Pay per article, scoped to content IDs"},{t:"Gift",d:"Shareable unlock links, time-limited"},{t:"Institutional",d:"Libraries, universities, organizations"},{t:"Metered",d:"Free article limits with meter tracking"},{t:"Locale-free",d:"Regional free access by user locale"},{t:"Patronage",d:"Voluntary support, optional full access"},{t:"Broker",d:"Multi-publisher bundles via brokers"}] %}
      <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-zinc-900/5 hover:border-emerald-400/30 transition-colors">
        <h4 class="text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-0.5">{{ g.t }}</h4>
        <p class="text-xs text-zinc-500">{{ g.d }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Compatibility -->
<section class="py-20 border-t border-zinc-900/5">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mb-10">
      <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold text-zinc-900 mb-3">Compatibility</h2>
      <p class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-zinc-900">Works with what you already use</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-zinc-600 mt-3">OPE is a purely additive extension. Readers without OPE support simply see previews as usual.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      {% for tag in ["RSS 2.0", "Atom", "JSON Feed", "AT Protocol", "OAuth 2.0", "PKCE", "JWT", "PASETO", "Macaroons", "DPoP", "PAR / RAR", "HTTP 402", "RFC 7591", "x402", "Stripe", "WordPress", "Ghost"] %}
      <span class="rounded-full px-3 py-1 text-xs font-medium text-zinc-600 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-900/10">{{ tag }}</span>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="bg-zinc-900 py-20">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white mb-3">Start building with OPE</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-zinc-400 mb-8 max-w-md mx-auto">The specification is open and ready for implementers. Read it, build on it, and help shape portable entitlements for the open web.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-3">
      <a href="{{ '/ope/spec/' | url }}" class="rounded-full bg-emerald-500 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white hover:bg-emerald-400 no-underline transition-colors">Read the Specification</a>
      <a href="https://github.com/shellen/open-portable-entitlement" class="rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-400 ring-1 ring-inset ring-zinc-400/20 hover:text-white hover:ring-zinc-400/40 no-underline transition-colors">Contribute on GitHub</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
